(1) Grammar purists will complain about it. "at position" is clearer.

(2) I think Elliott's point is that it's dangerous to print a string that we rejected because we suspect users are fudging around with it. In this case you have an upper bound on the length so it's ok.

To look at it another way : The developers of the APK don't need to know *which* entry is wrong, do they ? It will take a few seconds to use zipinfo or unzip to get the answer. Also, the chances of this happening accidentally are remote...

